Angola’s Central Bank Sells $100 Million of Foreign Currency at Auction

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-03-24T04:48:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/angola-s-central-bank-sells-100-million-of-foreign-currency-at-auction.html
Angola ’s central bank sold $100
million at a foreign-currency auction held yesterday, Banco
Nacional de Angola said in an e-mailed statement.  The kwanza sold for 93.501 to the dollar at the auction,
unchanged from the previous sale on March 22. The bank’s
overnight lending rate dropped to 16.5 percent on March 22 from
17 percent March 15, the Luanda-based central bank said.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
